channel.title: Putting 667 RSPS online: Help V3
channel.description:
I really need help guys, i'm not understanding.. I've port forwarded but it's still not working.. If anyone has any idea's please post.. this is my third post on this topic.
What i've done:
- Portforwarded to default gateway website (192.168.1.1) - Downloaded/installed No-Ip Duc - Made a firewall exception, port: 43594 - Running the server while I try to see if it's online to other players (which its NOT)

item.title: Putting 667 RSPS online: Help V3
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

You don’t port forward to 192.168.1.1, you use 192.168.1.1 as the routers default gateway to connect to the router settings. You port forward to your internal IP address (the one you get from run > cmd > ipconfig ; IPV4). Is that what you’d meant?

Read full topic

item.title: Putting 667 RSPS online: Help V3
item.dc:creator: @Taharahora Taharahora
item.description:
@Taharahora wrote:

[quote=“couttiiee, post:2, topic:462438”]You can use
www.canyouseeme.org to tell if your server is online.

if it says it is offline you could have a program like utorrent open or maybe you didnt add the exception in your firewall corrently. a good way to tell is just turn all your fire wall off and test on canyouseeme to see if it turns on then.[/quote]

Can you see me .org doesn’t always state that port is opened it isn’t the best thing to use. My VPS has never said canyouseeme.org can see it, yet i can still connect.

OT: I can run 317 - 474’s but i can’t get any other revision running. so if you figure it out i’d like to know as well!
